<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4700] StreamsKafkaClient drops security configs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4700</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;`StreamsKafkaClient` takes a `StreamsConfig` and calls `values` on it to create a `ChannelBuilder`. `values` creates a `Map` with parsed values for &lt;em&gt;defined&lt;/em&gt; config names. `StreamsConfig` doesn&apos;t define security settings itself and hence the security configs are dropped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For `KafkaProducer` and `KafkaConsumer` used by Streams, there is some code that gets the original configs (using `originals` instead of `values`) and passes them to the `KafkaConsumer` and `KafkaProducer` constructors (both of which define the security configs).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The suggested solution is to create a config definition for `StreamsKafkaClient` thas includes a copy of the `StreamsConfig` definition combined with the security configs definitions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
